Hepatic transplantation in children using reduced size allografts.

Badger IL(1), Czerniak A, Beath S, Tisone G, Deakin M, Sherlock DJ, Kelly DA, 
McMaster P, Buckels JA.

Author information:
(1)Liver Unit, Queen Elizabeth Hospital, Edgbaston, Birmingham, UK.

The shortage of paediatric liver donors has led to the use of reduced size 
hepatic allografts. Between July 1987 and July 1990, 30 reduced size orthotopic 
liver transplantations were performed in 24 children aged between 3 months and 7 
years. All patients were in advanced chronic or acute liver failure and were 
